The paper proposes a regularization framework for variational autoencoders to ensure semantic validity in the generation of graphs. This involves formulating penalty terms that regularize the output distribution of the decoder to encourage the satisfaction of validity constraints. This work is relevant to several sub-categories of computer science, including machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), computer vision (cs.CV), social and information networks (cs.SI), and computational linguistics (cs.CL).
